  <div>
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">What's the difference between Oregon and California Pinot Noir under $20?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Oregon Pinot Noir under $20 typically shows more earthy, mushroom, and forest floor notes with higher acidity due to the cooler climate, while California versions tend to be fruit-forward with riper strawberry and cherry flavors. Oregon wines often have a more delicate structure, whereas California Pinots may display slightly more body and alcohol warmth. Both offer excellent value, but Oregon wines pair better with salmon and mushroom dishes, while California versions complement grilled meats and tomato-based cuisines.</p>
