  <div>
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">What vintage should I look for when buying Pinot Noir under $20?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">For wines under $20, stick to vintages from the past 2-3 years, as these wines are designed for early consumption and won't improve with extended aging. The 2021 and 2022 vintages are currently ideal for most regions, offering fresh fruit expression without any decline from oxidation. Avoid vintages older than 2019 unless they're from a particularly exceptional year or have been stored properly, as budget Pinots can lose their vibrant character relatively quickly.</p>
